reviewText: Perfect.  Suitably challenging for our age (mid 70's)  We're getting stronger, but no injuries.  A very safe, challenging routine.

I am turning 66 next month & enjoy working out in the convenience of my own home during the winter months. I absolutely love this Sue Grant workout - lots of different levels to pick from. I owned many Jane Fonda videos/CDs & was looking for a change. Sue Grant provides a wonderful new perspective for me. My CD library is only Sue Grant now. Would recommend this anyone over 50!!!
It is a good tape for toning and stretching muscles.
Good program, but not necessary to purchase level 1 and 2 as 3 and 4 are just more of the same
I like this one very much, even though it is quite similar to the earlier version from a few years ago.  A very good all-around workout that can be done at whatever intensity level works for you.
Energetic, fun ,but a little too  cutzie. I like the strength training part, challenging , i used different muscle groups.
Fantastic light aerobics video! Absolutely love the stretching section.  Very safe and effective workout.
Need to return dvd it freezes

This is a challenging workout for us.  As usual, 3 levels of intensity are given which is a great help.  The DVD is very well organized and Sue's instructions are timely and clear.  I would recommend this DVD to people who I know exercise regularly.
I think Sue Grant got better with each DVD she did, making levels 3 and 4 the best.  Level 4 also includes some from levels 1 and 2.
